accessibility.text: Understand frequently used terms in the tRPC ecosystem
Procedure - API endpoint, can be a query, mutation, or subscription.
Query - A procedure used to fetch data, generally does not change any data
Mutation - A procedure used to send data, often for create/update/delete purposes
Subscription - A procedure that creates a persistent connection and listen to changes, like WebSockets
Router - A collection of procedures (and/or other routers) under a shared namespace.
